  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39_21",
    "text": "Questions or Comments?",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.5338809066141879,
      0.5319767441430423,
      0.743326490819077,
      0.5436507934977771
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39_4",
    "text": "The internet has many resources to assist you - search for \"IC Manufacturers logos\" or \"SMD codes\" if you need more information. And look up \"EIA-96\" to decode SMD resistors with what looks like a weird 2-number plus 1-letter code.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.06981518955489022,
      0.5334302325514725,
      0.5030800739880191,
      0.5873015871453477
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39",
    "order": 15
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39_22",
    "text": "Do you have technical questions or comments about his article? Email the author at stn564@yahoo.com.au or contact Elektor at editor@elektor.com.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5318275147189828,
      0.5478670635868508,
      0.9383983404952657,
      0.5873015872240783
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39",
    "order": 16
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39_5",
    "text": "Consider the Context",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.07186858050120068,
      0.6031746029392432,
      0.25667351025855295,
      0.6133720929199105
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39",
    "order": 17
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39_6",
    "text": "If you're stripping parts off boards, or otherwise know where the component came from, that may give you a clue as to what the part is. A power supply is likely to have a switched-mode PWM IC, whereas an audio board is more likely to have op-amps.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.0698152003309406,
      0.6191860466331416,
      0.5030800624342893,
      0.6729651161767252
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39",
    "order": 18
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_enbook-zlib-o.O-21353024.pdf_39_23",
    "text": "RELATED PRODUCTS",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
